{
  "title": "Method of hub communication",
  "abstract": "Disclosed is a surgical system, comprising surgical hubs configured to be communicatively coupled to surgical instruments in surgical procedures; and a cloud computing system, comprising an input/output interface configured for accessing data from the surgical hubs. The cloud computing system is configured to aggregate surgical instrument data and patient outcome date from the surgical hubs; determine a correlation between the surgical instrument data and the patient outcome data; access a live surgical procedure data for a live surgical procedure; and determine an irregularity in the live surgical procedure data based on the correlation.",
  "claims": "1. A surgical system, comprising: surgical hubs configured to be communicatively coupled to surgical instruments in surgical procedures; a user portal; and a cloud computing system, comprising an input/output interface configured for accessing data from the surgical hubs, wherein the cloud computing system is configured to: aggregate surgical instrument data and patient outcome data from the surgical hubs; identify a correlation between the surgical instrument data and the patient outcome data; receive live surgical procedure data of a surgical instrument during a live surgical procedure performed by the surgical instrument; determine that a control program for the surgical instrument is dictating a force to fire for the surgical instrument that is suboptimal for a particular tissue type being operated on based on the live surgical procedure data and the correlation; generate a recommendation to update the control program of the surgical instrument based on the determination that the control program of the surgical instrument is dictating the force to fire for the surgical instrument that is suboptimal for the particular tissue type being operated on; and automatically update the control program of the surgical instrument based on the generated recommendation the updated control program dictates a force to fire for the surgical instrument that is optimal for the particular tissue type being operated on for a remainder of the live surgical procedure.",
  "patent_id": "US12381936-20250805",
